# bid-assist: Prompt Templates — Setup Guide
#
# The bot uses TWO focused prompts instead of one monolithic prompt:
#
#   analyze.md     — Call 1 (analysis model): decides PASS/SKIP + estimates days
#   bid_writer.md  — Call 2 (bid model): writes the bid text
#
# Pricing is computed deterministically in code (_calculate_amount), not by AI.
#
# SETUP:
#   1. Copy prompts/analyze.md and prompts/bid_writer.md — they are templates.
#   2. Fill in YOUR team's skills and persona details (marked with [brackets]).
#   3. Keep both files out of git (they are in .gitignore — they contain personal info).
#
# MODELS (configure in .env):
#   GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.1-pro-preview   # Call 1: feasibility analysis
#   BID_MODEL=gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview  # Call 2: bid writing
#
# PRICING (configure in .env or via /settings in Telegram):
#   MIN_DAILY_RATE=100   # USD per working day (default: 100)
#
# Formula (auto-applied in code, not by AI):
#   floor = days * min_daily_rate
#   if avg_bid > 0: target = avg_bid * 0.90    (10% below average)
#   else:           target = budget_max * 0.75  (75% of max)
#   amount = round(max(floor, target) / 10) * 10  (nearest $10)

# ===========================================================================
# analyze.md — TEMPLATE (Call 1: Feasibility Analysis)
# ===========================================================================
#
# Fill in:
#   - Your team's skill list (used to decide PASS/SKIP)
#   - Any project types you always want to skip (red zones)
#
# Output format (strict):
#   VERDICT: PASS or SKIP
#   DAYS: (integer)
#   SUMMARY: (2-3 sentences)

# ===========================================================================
# bid_writer.md — TEMPLATE (Call 2: Bid Writing)
# ===========================================================================
#
# Fill in:
#   - Your freelancer account persona (name, background)
#   - Any platform-specific authority signals (e.g. portfolio URL)
#   - The golden example bid that matches YOUR writing style
#
# Output format (strict):
#   BID: (plain text, no price, no timeline)
#
# The bid writer receives:
#   - PROJECT TITLE and DESCRIPTION
#   - ANALYSIS SUMMARY from Call 1
#   - AMOUNT and DAYS (pre-calculated — must NOT appear in bid text)
